Katie Sales

sales = read.csv("http://fdrennan.net/pages/pages2/datasets/sales.csv")
sales = sales[1:105,]
sales$stores = substring(sales$Invoice, 9)
uniqueStores = unique(sales$stores)
sales$Total.Sales = sub("\\$", "", sales$Total.Sales)
sales$Total.Sales = as.numeric(sales$Total.Sales)
sales$Date = as.Date(sales$Date, "%m/%d/%Y")
datesTicks = seq(as.Date("01-01-2017", "%m-%d-%Y"), as.Date("10-01-2017", "%m-%d-%Y"), "months")

for(store in uniqueStores) {
  storeData = subset(sales, store == sales$stores)
  plot(storeData$Date, storeData$Total.Sales, 
       title = store, 
       type = "b", 
       ylim = c(0, max(sales$Total.Sales)), 
       xlim = c(min(unique(sales$Date)),max(unique(sales$Date))),
                main = store,
  xlab = "Date",
  ylab = "Total Sales", xaxt = "n")
  axis.Date(1, at=datesTicks, labels=as.character(datesTicks))
}
